Task: Build a fully functional, state-driven "Deployments" tab for Corefinity that strictly follows the sequential logic requirements.
​1. The Sequential Form (Core Requirement):
​Create a "Connect New Repository" card.
​State Machine Logic: Implement four dropdowns with the following strict dependency chain:
​Pipeline Type (Web, Worker, Cron)
​Provider (GitHub, Bitbucket, GitLab) - Disabled until Pipeline is selected.
​Repository (Mock list of repos) - Disabled until Provider is selected.
​Branch (main, develop, staging) - Disabled until Repository is selected.
​Validation Message: If 'GitHub' is selected as the Provider, display a high-visibility warning: "⚠️ No account connected. [Link GitHub Account]" (Use the OrangeLink for the link).
​2. Live Deployment Simulation:
​Create a "Recent Deployment Tasks" table.
​Top Row Interaction: The most recent task should show a status of "Deploying..." with a pulsing green dot and a real Progress Bar that animates from 0% to 100% over 10 seconds.
​Action Buttons: Add a "Rollback" button to previous successful deployments. When clicked, show a "Confirm Rollback" modal.
​3. Technical UI Details:
​Include columns for: Commit Hash (e.g., a7b2c3d in monospace font), Commit Message, Author (with avatar), and Duration.
​Every Repository name and Environment ID must be rendered in Corefinity Orange (#FF6B00).
​4. Implementation Detail:
​Use React useState to track the currentStep of the form.
​Ensure the "Deploy" button is only clickable once all 4 fields are filled.
​On "Deploy" click, trigger a toast notification: "Deployment Started Successfully."
